content:
The Property line of business provides a fully functional example of Homeowners and Renters product models, rating procedures, and business processes for quoting, issuing, modifying, and canceling policies.

This guide will orient you to the contents of the org and the business process for personal property insurance.

Product Models and Rating Procedures

* Product Model: Homeowners (HO3)
* Rating Procedure: propHO3RatingProcedure
* Product Model: Renters (HO4)
* Rating Procedure: propHO4RatingProcedure

The product models provide the structure for the data JSON that moves through the business processes. The rating procedures take information from the prospective customer and calculate prices for coverages.

Business Processes

* Homeowners Quote
* Issue Policy
* Cancel Policy

Homeowners Quote includes sub-processes, such as emailing quote documents to a prospect.

Now that you've got a high-level intro to Property, take a look at:

* Property Product Model
* Property Rating
* State Models
* Property Quote Business Process
* Issue Policy Business Processes
* Renew Policy Business Process
* Cancel Policy Business Process
* Direct Billing and Auto Pay
* One-Time Payment for Policy Premium
title: Understanding Property Insurance Line of Business
